00042 void test(bool indexed)
00043 {
00044     if (os_) *os_ << "test(): indexed=\"" << boolalpha << indexed << "\"\n";
00045

00059 
00060     // dummy would normally be read in from file

00065     pg1->id = "CommonMS1SpectrumParams";
00066     pg1->cvParams.push_back(MS_positive_scan);
00067     pg1->cvParams.push_back(MS_full_scan);
00068     dummy.paramGroupPtrs.push_back(pg1);
00069 
00070     ParamGroupPtr pg2(new ParamGroup);
00071     pg2->id = "CommonMS2SpectrumParams";
00072     pg2->cvParams.push_back(MS_positive_scan);
00073     pg2->cvParams.push_back(MS_full_scan);
00074     dummy.paramGroupPtrs.push_back(pg2);
00075 
00076     // so we don't have any dangling references
00077     dummy.instrumentPtrs.push_back(InstrumentPtr(new Instrument("LCQ Deca")));
00078     dummy.dataProcessingPtrs.push_back(DataProcessingPtr(new DataProcessing("Xcalibur Processing")));
00079 
00080     SpectrumListPtr sl = SpectrumList_mzML::create(is, dummy, indexed);
00081 
00082     // check easy functions
00083 
00084     unit_assert(sl.get());

00086     unit_assert(sl->find ("S19") == 0);
00087     unit_assert(sl->findNative("19") == 0);
00088     unit_assert(sl->find("S20") == 1);
00089     unit_assert(sl->findNative("20") == 1);
00090 
00091     // check scan 19
00092 
00093     SpectrumPtr s = sl->spectrum(0); // read without binary data
00094     unit_assert(s.get());
00095     unit_assert(s->id == "S19");
00096     unit_assert(s->nativeID == "19");
00097     unit_assert(s->cvParam(MS_ms_level).valueAs<int>() == 1);
00098     unit_assert(s->binaryDataArrayPtrs.empty());
00099 
00100     unit_assert(sl->spectrumIdentity(0).index == 0);
00101     unit_assert(sl->spectrumIdentity(0).id == "S19");
00102     unit_assert(sl->spectrumIdentity(0).nativeID == "19");
00103  
00104     SpectrumPtr s_cache = sl->spectrum(0); // cache read
00105     unit_assert(s_cache.get() == s.get());
00106 
00107     s = sl->spectrum(0, true); // read with binary data
00108     unit_assert(s_cache.get() != s.get());
00109 
00110     vector<MZIntensityPair> pairs;
00111     s->getMZIntensityPairs(pairs);
00112     unit_assert(pairs.size() == 15);
00113     for (int i=0; i<15; i++)
00114         unit_assert(pairs[i].mz==i && pairs[i].intensity==15-i);
00115 
00116     unit_assert(s->spectrumDescription.scan.paramGroupPtrs.size() == 1);
00117     unit_assert(s->spectrumDescription.scan.paramGroupPtrs.back()->id == "CommonMS1SpectrumParams");
00118     unit_assert(s->spectrumDescription.scan.paramGroupPtrs.back()->cvParams.size() == 2);
00119 
00120     // check scan 20
00121 
00122     s = sl->spectrum(1, true);
00123     unit_assert(s.get());
00124     unit_assert(s->id == "S20");
00125     unit_assert(s->nativeID == "20");
00126     unit_assert(s->cvParam(MS_ms_level).valueAs<int>() == 2);
00127 
00128     unit_assert(sl->spectrumIdentity(1).index == 1);
00129     unit_assert(sl->spectrumIdentity(1).id == "S20");
00130     unit_assert(sl->spectrumIdentity(1).nativeID == "20");
00131 
00132     pairs.clear();
00133     s->getMZIntensityPairs(pairs);
00134     unit_assert(pairs.size() == 10);
00135     for (int i=0; i<10; i++)
00136         unit_assert(pairs[i].mz==2*i && pairs[i].intensity==(10-i)*2);
00137 
00138     unit_assert(s->spectrumDescription.scan.paramGroupPtrs.size() == 1);
00139     unit_assert(s->spectrumDescription.scan.paramGroupPtrs.back()->id == "CommonMS2SpectrumParams");
00140     unit_assert(s->spectrumDescription.scan.paramGroupPtrs.back()->cvParams.size() == 2);
